anism is robust.\n\n**Advice to Avoid Syntax Errors:**\n*   When capturing signal values in the clocked block, ensure the assignment happens *after* the comparison logic has determined the mismatch, and use non-blocking assignments (`<=`) for storage registers, as these registers are effectively part of the sequential logic.\n*   The original comparison `tb_match = ( { q_ref, state_ref } === ( { q_ref, state_ref } ^ { q_dut, state_dut } ^ { q_ref, state_ref } ) );` is functionally equivalent to `tb_match = ( { q_ref, state_ref } === { q_dut, state_dut } );`. I will simplify this to the direct equality check for readability while preserving functionality.\n*   The `stimulus_gen` task usage is highly specific to the original TB and must be preserved exactly.\n\n**Implementation Details:** I will use dedicated variables (`fail_time`, `fail_q_time`, etc.) and corresponding signal capture registers (`snap_a`, `snap_q_dut`, etc.) to log the state at the time of the first failure.",
